  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted spanning all five flow-speed operating points; Latin hypercube sampling over 128 design-of-experiment runs established that impeller tip clearance and inlet swirl angle are the dominant sensitivity drivers, collectively accounting for 74% of the variance in the relative hemolysis index. These UQ findings informed the final worst-case operating-condition selection and are documented in the validation report referenced below.",
