      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations (RANS k-omega SST, power-law hemolysis damage model) justified by literature precedent and sensitivity to model-form assumptions documented.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating blood-contacting devices (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model validated against NIH data. Model-form sensitivity to turbulence model choice explored in the UQ campaign by comparing SST against realizable k-epsilon on the nominal geometry; RH difference of 4.2% is within validation uncertainty. Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
