      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary condition inputs documented with sources and uncertainty ranges; nominal inputs traceable to measurement or literature.",
      "rationale": "Blood density, viscosity (Carreau-Yasuda parameters), and hematocrit sourced from published literature with uncertainty ranges. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream pipe flow measurements. Impeller rotational speed from motor encoder data ± 0.5 RPM. All inputs tabulated in the simulation data package. The 128-run LHS UQ campaign propagated input uncertainties through the model to rank sensitivity; tip clearance and inlet swirl angle identified as dominant. Level 2 achieved."
